Museum to install talking CCTV

Talking CCTV cameras could be introduced at one of the Black Country's top
tourist attractions, it was revealed today.

The Black Country Living Museum would be the first place in Dudley borough
to install the new crimebusting Big Brother devices in a modern attempt to
solve an age-old problem.

Moves to beef up security at the museum in Tipton Road comes after an arson
attack on a builders' shed and the theft of a dog after a visitor's car was
broken into within less than a week.

A security guard at the site would be able to shout warnings through a
speaker attached to the camera if anyone was spotted misbehaving.

Read the full story in the Express & Star.

http://www.expressandstar.co.uk/




